<xar:template compile="false" file="mod-admin-title" type="module" />
<!--- END TITLE BAR -------------------------------------------------------------  --->
<div class="xar-mod-body" style="display:block;">
  <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>
  <div style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #B3B3B3; padding: 1px;">
    <div style="float:right;display:block;background-color:#ffffff;padding:10px;">
	    <xar:set name="$modInfo">xarModGetInfo(xarModGetIDFromName(__ADDRESSBOOK__))</xar:set>
          <img src="modules/#$modInfo['directory']#/xarimages/admin.gif" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
    </div>
		<div class="xar-mod-title" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-width: 1px; border-color: #B3B3B3; border-style: none none dotted none;">
			 <xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring>
		</div>
    <br />

		<div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;"> <xar:mlstring>The AddressBook was inspired by the Palm V PDA and gives your site to ability to have a single, shared contact list of
      multiple private address lists for each registered user.</xar:mlstring>
      <ul>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Fully Xaraya compliant.</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Flexible categories &amp; contact labels</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Add custom fields for each entry</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Full text search</xar:mlstring></li>
        <li><xar:mlstring>Image support for each contact</xar:mlstring></li>
      </ul>
		</div>
		<br />
		<div class="xar-mod-title" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-width: 1px; border-color: #B3B3B3; border-style: none none dotted none;">
		<xar:mlstring>User Features</xar:mlstring>		</div>
		<br />
		<div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
		<table width="80%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
		  <tr align="left" valign="top">
		    <td><ul>
		      <li><xar:mlstring>Each address entry can be categorized</xar:mlstring></li>
		      <li><xar:mlstring>Up to 5 contact labels per address</xar:mlstring></li>
		      <li><xar:mlstring>Free choice for primary contact (shown in list view)</xar:mlstring></li>
		      <li><xar:mlstring>The list of addresses can be narrowed by selecting an individual category</xar:mlstring></li>
		      <li><xar:mlstring>Address record sorting can be configured multiple ways</xar:mlstring></li>
		      <li><xar:mlstring>Unlimited optional fields</xar:mlstring></li>
		      <li><xar:mlstring>Custom textarea field width is configurable</xar:mlstring></li>
		      <li><xar:mlstring>Configurable main menu</xar:mlstring></li>
		      </ul></td>
		    <td><ul>
		      <li><xar:mlstring>Free format note field for each contact</xar:mlstring></li>
		      <li><xar:mlstring>Autofill company address by lookup feature</xar:mlstring></li>
		      <li><xar:mlstring>Copy to clipboard feature (Internet Explorer only)</xar:mlstring></li>
		      <li><xar:mlstring>Autodetect mail and url contact labels</xar:mlstring></li>
		      <li><xar:mlstring>Global and/or private contacts</xar:mlstring></li>
		      <li><xar:mlstring>Show zip before city (Europe) option</xar:mlstring></li>
		      </ul></td>
		    </tr>
		  </table>
		</div>
		<br />
		<div class="xar-mod-title" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-width: 1px; border-color: #B3B3B3; border-style: none none dotted none;">
					<xar:mlstring>Admin Notes</xar:mlstring>
		</div>
		<br />
		<div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
		<p><xar:mlstring>As an admin you should have access to all records of all users in the Address Book. 
		Therefore the &quot;Show private contacts&quot; switch works different for the admin than for other 
		users. If it set to &quot;on&quot;, all records you have entered are shown, if it is set to &quot;off&quot; 
		all records aof all users are shown. A registered user will see only his own records marked as private.
		So if you test the Address Book, create a user account and log in	as a normal user.</xar:mlstring></p><xar:mlstring>
		<p>As an Admin you will see the always the full main menu with all options, regardless of any setting that 
		was made in the Administration.</xar:mlstring><p></p>
		<p><xar:mlstring>For additional information consult the admin</xar:mlstring> <a href="#xarModURL(__ADDRESSBOOK__,'admin','displaydocs')#"><xar:mlstring>documentation</xar:mlstring></a></p>
		</div>
		<br />
		<div class="xar-mod-title" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-width: 1px; border-color: #B3B3B3; border-style: none none dotted none;">
			<xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring>
  	</div>
		<div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
			<ul>
				<li><xar:mlstring>none right now</xar:mlstring><br />
		</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
